{
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "concepts_pnpm_recursive_build_verification",
      "label": "pnpm Recursive Build Verification",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\pnpm-recursive-build-verification.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:36:30.814Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Recursive build verification confirms the workspace dependency graph resolves correctly and each package's build tooling executes properly. The -r flag runs pnpm across all workspace packages in dependency order, ensuring packages with dependencies are built after their dependencies."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_pnpm_workspace_architecture",
      "label": "pnpm Workspace Architecture",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\pnpm-workspace-architecture.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:39:16.488Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Monorepo structure with pnpm workspaces enables code sharing between frontend and backend while maintaining clear boundaries between application layers. The apps/* and packages/* pattern separates deployable applications from internal libraries."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_pnpm_workspace_configuration",
      "label": "pnpm Workspace Configuration",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\pnpm-workspace-configuration.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:19:18.554Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Standard pnpm workspace layout uses apps/* and packages/* globs in pnpm-workspace.yaml. Root package.json pins packageManager to pnpm@8.15.0 and requires Node >=20 for consistent tooling across the workspace."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_pnpm_workspace_monorepo",
      "label": "pnpm Workspace Monorepo",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\pnpm-workspace-monorepo.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:36:48.469Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "pnpm workspace monorepo enables centralized dependency management, shared tooling, and atomic commits across related projects. The workspace: protocol ensures local package changes are immediately reflected without publishing to a registry."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_presigned_url_security_pattern",
      "label": "Presigned URL Security Pattern",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\presigned-url-security-pattern.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:38:17.000Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Defense-in-depth is achieved through time-bounded access (5-min upload TTL, 15-min download TTL), content-type restrictions, UUID-based object key isolation, and optional IP/User-Agent restrictions. The GCS bucket remains private; only signed URLs grant access."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_presigned_url_upload_pattern",
      "label": "Presigned URL Upload Pattern",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\presigned-url-upload-pattern.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:37:31.250Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "The pattern bypasses Vercel's serverless function body size limits (4.5MB Hobby, 6MB Pro) by having browsers upload directly to GCS. HWP files with embedded images commonly exceed these limits, making presigned URLs the only viable upload mechanism."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_redis_job_queue_system",
      "label": "Redis Job Queue System",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\redis-job-queue-system.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:38:25.159Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Redis-based job tracking with 2-hour TTL is sufficient because the Cloud Run conversion worker runs with concurrency=1 (LibreOffice is single-process), so no additional queue synchronization is needed. TTL-based cleanup eliminates the need for a dedicated cleanup worker."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_serverless_rate_limiting",
      "label": "Serverless Rate Limiting",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\serverless-rate-limiting.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:38:05.717Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "In-memory rate limiting fails in serverless because each function instance has independent memory. A user with 60 req/hr limit can effectively use 180 req/hr across 3 instances. Upstash Redis HTTP API is the recommended solution because it avoids persistent connections."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_session_based_documentation",
      "label": "Session-Based Documentation",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\session-based-documentation.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:40:09.064Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Dated session notes provide a verifiable record of what was actually executed and succeeded, complementing the principle of preferring verified executable sources over potentially outdated documentation."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_session_documentation_rule",
      "label": "Session Documentation Rule",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\session-documentation-rule.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:37:30.903Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Mandatory session note creation after successful code/config changes maintains a searchable history for both human contributors and AI assistants. Conciseness is prioritized over verbosity."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_shared_package_architecture",
      "label": "Shared Package Architecture",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\shared-package-architecture.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:36:43.045Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Centralizing utilities in a single shared package reduces duplication, ensures consistency across consumers, and propagates changes (e.g., file size limits) automatically to all dependents."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_shared_typescript_contracts_package",
      "label": "Shared TypeScript Contracts Package",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\shared-typescript-contracts-package.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:36:44.702Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "TypeScript Compiler is sufficient as the build tool because the package primarily exports types and utility functions, not complex bundled code. The dist/ output provides full type safety to consumers."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_shared_typescript_contracts",
      "label": "Shared TypeScript Contracts",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\shared-typescript-contracts.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:19:34.695Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Single source of truth for TypeScript contracts prevents type drift between frontend and backend. The 20MB size limit and .hwp-only restriction are policy decisions enforced through shared code."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_upstash_rate_limiting",
      "label": "Upstash Rate Limiting",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\upstash-rate-limiting.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:38:39.925Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Upstash Redis HTTP API is serverless-friendly (no persistent connections needed). The sliding window algorithm provides balanced accuracy and the 60 req/hr limit is per IP for abuse prevention. X-Forwarded-For handling is critical behind proxies."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_vercel_oidc_federation",
      "label": "Vercel OIDC Federation",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\vercel-oidc-federation.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:37:47.572Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "OIDC Federation eliminates the need to store, rotate, and secure static Service Account key files. Short-lived, automatically-rotated tokens reduce attack surface. Audience claim must exactly match Cloud Run URL for security."
    },
    {
      "id": "concepts_verified_build_commands",
      "label": "Verified Build Commands",
      "file_type": "concept",
      "source_file": "C:\\NEW PRG\\HWP2PDF\\wiki\\concepts\\verified-build-commands.md",
      "source_location": null,
      "source_url": null,
      "captured_at": "2026-06-12T16:39:05.962Z",
      "author": null,
      "contributor": null,
      "rationale": "Commands must be verified as working before being documented. Unverified scripts (dev:api, build:api, typecheck, test) should not be relied upon without first confirming the target package and script exist."
    },
